                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On January 27, 1951, the Turkish Cabinet approved the dispatch of replacement
                    soldiers to Korea to reinforce the Turkish brigade fighting there under the
                    auspices of the United Nations Command. For documentation regarding the Korean
                    War and the treatment of United States–Turkish relations in the Korean context,
                    see <ref target="frus1951v07p1#pg_1">volume VII, pages 1</ref> ff.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
